WEBVTT

00:02.836 --> 00:03.837
[ Remote clicks ]

00:03.871 --> 00:05.406
[ Upbeat music plays ]

00:07.941 --> 00:10.844
♪ I don't care what you say!

00:12.180 --> 00:14.148
♪ I'm gonna do what I want
all day! ♪

00:14.182 --> 00:16.750
♪ I'm the king of the world!
I'm the king of the world! ♪

00:16.784 --> 00:18.686
♪ I'm the king of the world!
I'm the king of the world! ♪

00:18.719 --> 00:22.022
♪ I'm the king of the world!
I'm the king of the world! ♪

00:25.259 --> 00:29.597
♪♪

00:29.630 --> 00:30.731
[ Laughing ]

00:30.764 --> 00:32.733
Okay, see if you can hit
this one!

00:32.766 --> 00:34.168
Come on, come on!

00:34.202 --> 00:35.436
[ Chuckles ]

00:35.469 --> 00:38.072
Okay, here it comes!
Look out!

00:38.106 --> 00:39.373
[ Grunts ]

00:39.407 --> 00:40.741
Uh-oh, you missed!

00:40.774 --> 00:42.410
[ Grunts ]
Ah!

00:42.443 --> 00:43.777
Ah, so close!

00:43.811 --> 00:46.580
Okay, Sumo, try this.

00:46.614 --> 00:49.517
Ah!
[ Grunting ]

00:49.550 --> 00:53.121
Okay, come on, more, more!
[ Laughs ]

00:53.154 --> 00:55.256
[ Grunts ]

00:55.289 --> 00:58.359
Wha! Yeah!

00:58.392 --> 00:59.760
[ Glass shatters ]

00:59.793 --> 01:03.764
[ Alarm beeping ]

01:03.797 --> 01:05.233
Oh.
[ Groans ]

01:05.266 --> 01:06.267
Bye, guys.

01:06.300 --> 01:07.568
We can't just leave!

01:07.601 --> 01:09.069
That's gross negligence!

01:09.103 --> 01:11.071
Yeah, well, you threw it.

01:11.105 --> 01:14.108
Oh, so it's my fault
we're going to get arrested?

01:14.142 --> 01:16.744
It's okay, Jeff!
Maybe you didn't break anything!

01:16.777 --> 01:18.879
And it's okay.
Everything's fine!

01:18.912 --> 01:22.150
[ Grunting ]

01:24.818 --> 01:28.389
Um, excuse me,
did my friend break your stuff?!

01:28.422 --> 01:31.425
Guys, we shouldn't be in here!
Let's go!

01:31.459 --> 01:33.794
[ Grunts, screams ]

01:33.827 --> 01:35.896
It's okay --
I've done this before.

01:35.929 --> 01:37.798
My no-eyes senses
are pretty good.

01:37.831 --> 01:39.267
Oh, careful.

01:39.300 --> 01:41.935
I think there's a real big tiger
over here or something.

01:41.969 --> 01:43.971
-Ah, jeez!
-Stop.

01:44.004 --> 01:47.508
The door -- right behind you.
Open the door!

01:47.541 --> 01:50.144
Oh! Oh, my gosh!
I am so sorry.

01:50.178 --> 01:51.845
My friends
weren't paying attenti--

01:51.879 --> 01:53.281
Open the door!

01:53.314 --> 01:54.315
Okay, okay, okay!

01:54.348 --> 01:55.149
[ Grunting ]

01:55.183 --> 01:58.186
See, open!
-Whew! Good.

01:58.219 --> 02:00.988
Now the excess vapors
can properly escape.

02:01.021 --> 02:02.856
Huh?

02:02.890 --> 02:03.857
My name's Lauren.
[ Alarm stops ]

02:03.891 --> 02:05.359
Are you boys lost?

02:05.393 --> 02:07.628
If you're strangers,
you have to leave.

02:07.661 --> 02:10.164
Oh, oh, ah. Uh, no.

02:10.198 --> 02:12.866
We were just making sure
everything was all right.

02:12.900 --> 02:14.468
Yeah, 'cause
Jeff broke your window.

02:14.502 --> 02:16.136
-[ Stammers ]
-Oh!

02:16.170 --> 02:18.639
You must be the ones who were
making the noise out back.

02:18.672 --> 02:21.875
This must be yours.
Would you like your walnut back?

02:21.909 --> 02:23.677
Oh, yeah, thanks!
I hit it through the--

02:23.711 --> 02:26.514
Sumo! Okay, look --
we don't need the walnut back.

02:26.547 --> 02:28.682
We just need to know
if we are being punished or not.

02:28.716 --> 02:31.752
-Punished?
-Uh-huh, punished.

02:32.720 --> 02:34.222
-Jeff?
-Punished.

02:34.255 --> 02:35.456
Wait, what?

02:35.489 --> 02:37.291
Jeff -- I remember you!

02:37.325 --> 02:38.692
Come here.

02:38.726 --> 02:40.127
See!

02:40.160 --> 02:41.362
We were in Ms. Koyaanisqati's
class together --

02:41.395 --> 02:44.332
at least for a little bit,
anyway.

02:44.365 --> 02:45.366
Oh, yeah.

02:45.399 --> 02:49.136
I heard you left
'cause you, uh, got lice.

02:49.169 --> 02:51.205
Oh.
Isn't that bugs?

02:51.239 --> 02:53.374
Oh, that's not accurate
at all.

02:53.407 --> 02:56.076
My dad thought I wasn't getting
a good enough education,

02:56.109 --> 02:58.579
so he started
home-schooling me.

02:58.612 --> 03:01.249
Ew!
Your dad gives you grades?

03:01.282 --> 03:05.886
Oh, I don't get those.
I just hold myself accountable.

03:05.919 --> 03:08.822
So...
your home is your school...

03:08.856 --> 03:11.058
and your dad's
your teacher?

03:11.091 --> 03:14.161
And the whole world
is your playground?!

03:14.194 --> 03:16.664
Ha ha!
I've never heard it called that.

03:16.697 --> 03:18.732
Here, I'll show you.

03:18.766 --> 03:19.833
Gather around.

03:19.867 --> 03:21.235
I made this pH indicator

03:21.269 --> 03:23.737
by blending some red cabbage
in tap water.

03:23.771 --> 03:27.007
It changes color according
to a substance's pH levels.

03:27.040 --> 03:28.242
Whoa!
Wow!

03:28.276 --> 03:31.412
Did you know
that's because of the bubbles?

03:31.445 --> 03:32.846
Yeah, more specifically,

03:32.880 --> 03:36.917
the carbonic acid in soda reacts
with a pigment in the cabbage.

03:36.950 --> 03:39.720
Hmm.
Called anthro...

03:39.753 --> 03:41.622
Anthes -- antha...

03:41.655 --> 03:42.923
Anthocyanin!

03:42.956 --> 03:45.025
[ Chuckles ]
I always forget that word.

03:45.058 --> 03:47.027
Ha.
Me, too.

03:47.060 --> 03:50.097
And if we try
something more base, like...

03:50.130 --> 03:51.632
this baking soda...

03:51.665 --> 03:53.734
[ Laughs ]
It's different!

03:53.767 --> 03:55.303
What else you got?

03:55.336 --> 03:57.305
Let's see. Ah!

03:57.338 --> 03:59.873
I do have this clock
that runs on a potato.

03:59.907 --> 04:04.077
Oh, my goodness!
A potato!

04:04.111 --> 04:06.614
Ha ha!
That's a clock?

04:06.647 --> 04:09.450
[ Laughs ]

04:09.483 --> 04:12.085
[ Laughing harder ]

04:16.657 --> 04:18.926
Gee, I guess you don't have
batteries around here.

04:18.959 --> 04:21.295
Wow! If this is what you do
for school,

04:21.329 --> 04:23.897
what you do for playing
must be crazy!

04:23.931 --> 04:27.301
♪♪

04:29.937 --> 04:31.839
[ Groans ]

04:31.872 --> 04:34.508
Don't worry.
That's just Kathy.

04:34.542 --> 04:36.109
She's not real bones.

04:36.143 --> 04:38.979
So do you get graded on this,
or something?

04:39.012 --> 04:40.914
And shouldn't we
clean up the kitchen?

04:40.948 --> 04:43.484
I got it!
It's a bunny.

04:43.517 --> 04:45.319
Clarence: [ Chuckles ]
I made a house.

04:45.353 --> 04:46.820
Sumo:
Check these babies out!

04:46.854 --> 04:49.657
They're perfect for claw attack!
[ Gasps ]

04:49.690 --> 04:51.158
[ Laughing maniacally ]

04:51.191 --> 04:52.493
That's funny, Sumo!

04:52.526 --> 04:54.261
I would never think
to adapt this game

04:54.294 --> 04:55.696
to a different play style.

04:55.729 --> 04:57.264
At least
not in that fashion.

04:57.297 --> 05:00.000
Oh, ha ha,
yeah, it's fashion.

05:00.033 --> 05:02.770
Ha!
Yeah, claw fashion.

05:02.803 --> 05:04.805
Meow!
[ Growls ]

05:04.838 --> 05:06.640
[ Grunting ]

05:06.674 --> 05:09.142
Is this all you have to do
around here?

05:09.176 --> 05:12.279
Yeah.
Do you guys want to watch TV?

05:12.312 --> 05:14.482
Oh...
We don't have one.

05:14.515 --> 05:16.617
I guess video games
are out of the question.

05:16.650 --> 05:19.487
Well, I'm learning
how to code my own.

05:19.520 --> 05:21.855
[ Grunting ]
Got any Cheezo's?

05:21.889 --> 05:23.857
Cheezo's?

05:23.891 --> 05:25.659
[ Gasps ]
[ Grunts ]

05:25.693 --> 05:27.194
You've never had Cheezo's?!

05:27.227 --> 05:29.563
I mean, I have cheese!

05:32.666 --> 05:34.001
[ All sniffing ]

05:34.034 --> 05:35.202
[ Fog horn blows ]
Ew!

05:35.235 --> 05:37.170
Smell's like
my middle brother's gym bag.

05:37.204 --> 05:39.873
No, no, no!
Something must be done!

05:39.907 --> 05:43.076
♪♪

05:45.212 --> 05:46.880
[ Birds chirping ]

05:46.914 --> 05:51.552
Wow. Huh.

05:51.585 --> 05:53.086
Whoa.

05:53.120 --> 05:54.555
Hydroponics.

05:54.588 --> 05:56.557
Lauren:
You know, Clarence,

05:56.590 --> 05:58.559
I don't really see the point
in this game.

05:58.592 --> 06:01.695
Listen, Lauren, I understand
where you're coming from.

06:01.729 --> 06:03.564
I used to be terrible
at playing,

06:03.597 --> 06:05.332
and,
thanks to these goofballs,

06:05.365 --> 06:07.401
I've learned the true value
of horsing around.

06:07.435 --> 06:09.703
It's why childhood
was invented.

06:09.737 --> 06:12.039
Okay, Lauren, get ready.

06:12.072 --> 06:13.674
[ Grunts ]

06:13.707 --> 06:15.743
Huh?

06:15.776 --> 06:17.745
Hmm.

06:17.778 --> 06:19.046
This one!

06:19.079 --> 06:22.082
All: Hit it!
Hit it! Hit it! Hit it!

06:22.115 --> 06:23.283
[ Grunts ]

06:23.316 --> 06:29.289
[ Dramatic music plays ]

06:29.322 --> 06:31.525
Ha ha -- touchdown!

06:31.559 --> 06:32.526
[ Cheering ]

06:32.560 --> 06:34.595
You pulverized that cabbage,
Lauren!

06:34.628 --> 06:37.264
Hey, Sumo!
Throw another one!

06:37.297 --> 06:39.933
You got it,
you party animal!

06:39.967 --> 06:42.069
Lauren,
let's take it easy here.

06:42.102 --> 06:44.204
[ Laughing ]
Batter up!

06:44.237 --> 06:45.606
[ Grunts ]

06:45.639 --> 06:46.774
[ Grunts ]

06:46.807 --> 06:48.275
[ Grunts ]

06:48.308 --> 06:50.611
You know what?
This is pretty nice.

06:50.644 --> 06:54.081
Yeah, I increased the phosphate
in the soil this year.

06:54.114 --> 06:57.451
♪♪

06:57.485 --> 07:01.421
Uh, Lauren, you should probably
get back to your lessons.

07:01.455 --> 07:03.791
Wouldn't want
to get you in trouble.

07:03.824 --> 07:05.292
Eh...
I can hang out some more.

07:05.325 --> 07:07.628
Good! We just gotta
sneak you out of here.

07:07.661 --> 07:11.632
Sneak me out?
I'm not a prisoner, Clarence!

07:11.665 --> 07:13.834
Come on.

07:13.867 --> 07:15.235
Clarence?

07:15.268 --> 07:17.137
[ Gasps ] Hurry up,
before we get caught!

07:17.170 --> 07:18.472
[ Laughing ]

07:18.506 --> 07:21.008
Clarence, wait!
Sumo, jailbreak!

07:21.041 --> 07:23.243
Oh! Yah!

07:23.276 --> 07:24.912
[ Laughing ]

07:24.945 --> 07:26.313
Hang on, Lauren.
I got this!

07:26.346 --> 07:28.516
♪ People think
I'm kind of weird ♪

07:28.549 --> 07:30.784
♪ 'Cause
I'm at a different school ♪

07:30.818 --> 07:32.653
♪ But if they
just got to know me ♪

07:32.686 --> 07:35.923
♪ They would see
I'm pretty cool ♪

07:35.956 --> 07:37.525
♪ I may seem kind of nervous

07:37.558 --> 07:40.327
♪ But look
beneath the surface ♪

07:40.360 --> 07:43.163
♪ And you'll see

07:43.196 --> 07:47.501
♪ I just wanna have some fun

07:47.535 --> 07:50.170
♪ I know
I'm not the only one ♪

07:50.203 --> 07:52.372
♪ Who feels the same

07:52.405 --> 07:55.475
♪ 'Cause when I'm hanging
with my friends ♪

07:55.509 --> 08:01.314
♪ I just wanna go
again and again ♪

08:01.348 --> 08:05.686
♪ I just wanna have some fun

08:05.719 --> 08:08.021
♪ I know
I'm not the only one ♪

08:08.055 --> 08:10.558
♪ Who feels the same

08:10.591 --> 08:13.861
♪ 'Cause when I'm hanging
with my friends ♪

08:13.894 --> 08:16.163
♪ I just wanna go again

08:16.196 --> 08:19.366
♪ And again
and again and again ♪

08:19.399 --> 08:21.301
♪ And again and again

08:21.334 --> 08:23.704
♪ And again and again

08:23.737 --> 08:26.874
[ Crazy laughter ]

08:26.907 --> 08:28.075
Okay.
Oh, wow.

08:28.108 --> 08:29.209
Sumo: Go, Lauren!

08:29.242 --> 08:31.311
[ Screaming, laughing ]

08:31.344 --> 08:33.313
Okay, uh, that's plenty.

08:33.346 --> 08:34.481
Yeah, yeah,
yeah, yeah!

08:34.514 --> 08:37.885
We've got
a, uh, situation?

08:37.918 --> 08:39.052
[ Birds chirping ]

08:39.086 --> 08:41.054
Vegetables!

08:41.088 --> 08:43.390
Uh, shh, shh.
Lauren, be quiet!

08:43.423 --> 08:44.725
[ Grunts ]
Huh?

08:44.758 --> 08:46.727
[ Laughing ]
Vegetables are everywhere!

08:46.760 --> 08:49.663
Okay, Lauren. I got you.
They're everywhere!

08:49.697 --> 08:53.100
[ Gasps ]
Oh, yeah, the mess.

08:53.133 --> 08:54.902
Vroom!

08:54.935 --> 08:57.938
Ah, Lauren, are you okay?
[ Laughing ]

08:57.971 --> 09:00.040
S-Stop!

09:00.073 --> 09:02.576
Guys,
I think we should bail.

09:02.610 --> 09:03.777
What? Why?

09:03.811 --> 09:06.580
[ Laughing ]

09:06.614 --> 09:08.415
Yeah.

09:08.448 --> 09:10.684
Let's bust open my ant farm!

09:10.718 --> 09:12.753
Nah, I think
we are, um, gonna go,

09:12.786 --> 09:14.187
but it was nice knowing ya,
Lauren!

09:14.221 --> 09:15.923
Probably won't be seeing you
for a while,

09:15.956 --> 09:19.059
since you're gonna be grounded
for, like, ever.

09:19.092 --> 09:21.561
Here, Lauren.
I know you love cabbage.

09:21.595 --> 09:22.963
Ooh!

09:22.996 --> 09:25.265
Time to make our exit, guys.

09:25.298 --> 09:28.936
[ Dramatic music plays ]

09:35.008 --> 09:36.910
Hi, Father!

09:36.944 --> 09:39.212
Okay, well, I, uh, bye.

09:39.246 --> 09:40.981
We're sorry,
Mr. Lauren's Dad!

09:41.014 --> 09:44.985
We just wanted to play, and
we didn't mean to make a mess

09:45.018 --> 09:47.621
and, and, and
then stop Lauren from learning!

09:47.655 --> 09:49.289
Yeah,
that was so much fun!

09:49.322 --> 09:51.091
Lauren,
don't make this worse.

09:51.124 --> 09:55.663
Hmm. Lauren, you and your
friends seem little wound up.

09:55.696 --> 09:58.098
Why don't we all sit down
and talk?

09:58.131 --> 09:59.299
But, first...

09:59.332 --> 10:01.969
this yogurt
needs refrigeration.

10:02.002 --> 10:04.137
[ Lauren giggling ]

10:04.171 --> 10:07.641
♪♪

10:07.675 --> 10:10.778
[ Sighs ] Okay,
let's get this over with.

10:10.811 --> 10:12.112
Go ahead.

10:12.145 --> 10:14.748
What are you doing?

10:14.782 --> 10:16.283
Oh, I thought...

10:16.316 --> 10:17.851
I'll just sit back down.

10:20.487 --> 10:22.155
[ Lauren whooping ]

10:22.189 --> 10:24.457
What?!
A puppet show!

10:24.491 --> 10:26.193
So what I'm hearing, Lauren,

10:26.226 --> 10:27.594
is that you're enjoying

10:27.627 --> 10:29.930
the structure
of your home-schooling,

10:29.963 --> 10:34.668
but you also have a need of less
structured play with your peers.

10:34.702 --> 10:37.170
That sounds very reasonable.

10:37.204 --> 10:38.672
Thank you for listening,
Father.

10:38.706 --> 10:40.808
I appreciate
when my needs are being met.

10:40.841 --> 10:44.511
I'm happy when I can understand
and meet your needs.

10:44.544 --> 10:46.947
This has been
a productive dialogue.

10:46.980 --> 10:50.483
Wow, you guys!
Today was amazing!

10:50.517 --> 10:53.721
I had so much fun!
Thank you for coming over!

10:53.754 --> 10:57.490
Yeah.
Okay.

10:57.524 --> 11:00.027
Bye, Lauren!
Bye!

11:00.060 --> 11:01.394
[ Groans ]

11:05.365 --> 11:05.733
♪ Early to bed

11:08.769 --> 11:11.438
♪ Early to rise

11:12.272 --> 11:14.775
♪ Picking my nose
